      "Heba picked up a strong rope made from the hair of ten brown coconuts. Then she threaded the scale very carefully so that two large copper plates could hang from each side and move when weight was added to either plate. She placed a black stone on the right plate while using her free hand to hold the left plate in place. Then she tugged the left plate downward to test the rope. Next, she placed the second stone on the left plate and stepped back. The scale's arms bobbed up and down until they aligned equally - neither plate was too high or too low from its sibling. Before Heba could acknowledge the balance, a husky man with olive skin appeared. His wavy brown hair and silver beard caught Heba's attention.",
