      "The water, finding nothing left to punish, gave up and became sand again.",
      "It became other things after that. It became hot glass that she crossed flat-footed and unhurried, because hurrying is what glass wants. It became bone, and she walked the bones the way she walked the market's broken cobbles on delivery mornings, reading each step before she spent it. Once - only once - it became a floor of copper scale-plates, thousands of them, every plate tipping under her weight, and she could not tell if the chamber was mocking her or saluting her.",
      "Her hands were bleeding when she touched the far door. She did not remember cutting them. The glass had taken its fee somewhere in the crossing, quietly, like a good pickpocket.",
      "She turned around. Eleven torches, ten faces, one whistle.",
      "Userhat looked at her the way a man looks at a bill he cannot argue with.",
      "\"Adequate,\" he said, and wrote on his tablet.",
      "In the market, Heba thought, we call that word \"sold.\"",
