      "Then the boy folded to the floor, and woke, and began to cry, and remembered nothing - not the walk, not the hall, not the word. The crocodiles would not come away from the walls until he was gone. The guards led him off wrapped in someone's cloak, and the whole way down the corridor he kept asking the same question, over and over, to anyone who would listen.",
      "\"Why are my feet cold? Why are my feet cold? Why are my feet cold?\"",
      "Nahara's tray trembled. Heba took it from her, and the two girls stood together in the torchlight, shoulder to shoulder, neither one willing to say the number out loud.",
      "Namoot's feather had circled the sun five times.",
      "Five, Heba thought, cold climbing her spine like a ladder. The omen said five.",
      "Something in the palace was counting down."
