      "\"The natron? It shows.\"",
      "\"The trials.\" He turned, and there was no charm on his face at all, and she realized she had never seen it fully undressed before. \"You took a blade for me, and this house repays you with a room that drowns you and a hallway that wears your mother's mouth. You should not have to suffer to be counted useful. My sisters were born counted. I was born counted. You - \"",
      "\"Stop.\" Heba's voice came out flat as a plate. \"I do not need pity. Not from a prince. Not from anyone. I have crossed that floor and walked through that dark, and I did it with my own feet, and if you pity me you make it smaller.\"",
      "Ahmose looked at her for a long moment.",
      "\"Good,\" he said. \"I was offering respect.\"",
      "The river went on below them, uninterested, carrying its boats.",
      "Oh, Heba thought, with the specific dismay of a merchant who has just watched a customer pay full price without haggling, on purpose, so she would remember him. Oh, no.",
      "\"Then I accept,\" she said, with dignity, and did not look at him, and he did not look at her, and both of them looked at the river, which had seen this before and snickered all the way to the sea.",
      "The horror came at supper, three nights later, wearing maroon.",
      "The royal family dined in the lesser hall now - the great one was being \"restored,\" which everyone understood to mean watched. Heba attended as the prince's scribe, seated below the dais with a reed pen and genuine duties, because Mata believed the best disguise was an honest one.",
      "Seket was mid-story. Something about combat drills, a broken practice spear, a soldier twice her size put on his back - she told it with her whole body, braids swinging, and the family laughed, and for the length of that laugh the palace almost felt like a house.",
      "Then, between one word and the next, Seket stopped.",
      "Her face stayed lit. Her hands stayed raised. But her mouth kept moving, and the voice that came out of it was not hers - it was dry and patient and pleased, a page turning in an empty room, and it fell into the laughter like a stone into soup.",
      "\"Three,\" it said.",
      "The hall went silent.",
      "Seket blinked. Her hands came down. She looked around at the wreckage of the laugh, at her mother's white face and her father's stillness and Tawet's fingers frozen halfway through a mocking gesture, and she frowned the honest frown of a girl who has missed a joke.",
      "\"What?\" she demanded. \"Why are you all staring? Finish your food. As I was saying - the spear broke, and - \"",
      "She told the rest of the story. It was funny. Nobody laughed.",
      "Heba sat below the dais with her reed pen hovering and her linen burning coal-hot against her ribs, and she did what she had been placed in that room to do. She listened.",
      "Seket's heart: galloping, bewildered, innocent.",
      "The queen's heart: locked up like a strongbox with something alive inside.",
      "The Pharaoh's heart: a great slow drum, and behind the drum, for just a moment, the sound of a second drummer keeping different time.",
      "And in the hall itself, in the air, in the space above the long table where no chest was - faint, unhurried, satisfied -",
