      "Heba wrote one word on her papyrus, in a neat column, under all the small lies.",
      "Three.",
      "Five, the feather had promised. Four, the sleeping boy had said. Now three, from the mouth of a laughing princess.",
      "Whatever was counting, it was no longer outside the family.",
